2026-07-09T05:05:15.0200900Z             "body": "## Summary\nAdd cryptographic verification that the SVG logo advertised in a BIMI DNS record matches the logo hash embedded in the Verified Mark Certificate (VMC). This ensures the DNS-advertised logo is the one the CA signed off on.\n\n## Key Changes\n- **Capture fetched SVG content**: Store the first successfully retrieved SVG logo during the logo URL validation phase so it can be verified against the certificate later.\n- **Pass SVG to VMC validation**: Thread the fetched SVG content through to the `ValidateVmc` method for hash comparison.\n- **Parse logotype extension**: Implement `ParseSubjectLogoHashes()` to extract hash values and algorithms from the RFC 3709 logotype extension (OID 1.3.6.1.5.5.7.1.12) in the VMC certificate.\n- **Verify hash match**: Implement `VerifyLogotypeHash()` to compute the hash of the retrieved SVG using algorithms found in the certificate (SHA-256, SHA-384, SHA-512, SHA-1) and compare against the embedded values.\n- **Enhanced reporting**: Add detailed messages indicating:\n  - When logo hash successfully matches the VMC\n  - When hash verification cannot be performed (SVG not retrieved or extension not present)\n  - When hash mismatch is detected (warning that retrieved SVG differs from signed logo)\n\n## Implementation Details\n- Uses `System.Formats.Asn1` for DER parsing of the logotype extension structure\n- Supports multiple hash algorithms via OID mapping\n- Gracefully handles parsing failures and unsupported algorithms\n- Only performs verification when both the SVG and logotype extension are available\n\nhttps://claude.ai/code/session_01UFEGmQy7TdJY8QLFhmh5HC",
